    "summary": "CP00-208 (RP06 DMS-core synthetic fixture tail + golden-case entrypoint descriptor pack, risk A, 10 units, RP06.P02.M06.S16-RP06.P02.M07.S03) is in a coherent implemented_pending_review state and does NOT overclaim production readiness (manifest production_ready:false; production_ready_flag is a label; Hermes emits production_ready_candidate only). Read-only source inspection (Read/Grep/Glob) confirms the 10 planned units map 1:1 to 10 descriptor-only guards (blocked-claim, rollback, retry, happy/denied/review unit-test descriptors, integration smoke, service entrypoint contract, request normalization, tenant boundary precheck). Descriptor-only / no-write / no-real-data boundaries are substantiated in service.js (freezeCp208Result with ~50 false runtime flags), validators.js (validateDmsCoreCp208SyntheticFixtureTailEntrypointDescriptor asserts every runtime flag false + no-leak guards), model.test.js, the validate script, the contract no_write_attestation, and README; there is no network/filesystem/process I/O anywhere in packages/dms/src. CP178+ hardening holds: forbidden_review_evidence matches the required reject-list, readiness auth-preflight passed (exit 0, 1450-byte valid-JSON stdout, not 0-byte), and no invalid review attempts are recorded. Claude is consistently bound as read-only independent reviewer and not final approver, and enterprise trust is not claimed from local validation. Hermes patterns appear only as deterministic control-plane review-packet/receipt descriptors (gate H06), not embedded product runtime. No P0/P1 defects found. Remaining items are governance gating reminders that, by the pack's own design, run after this review in the hardening sequence (populate command-evidence with passing validation runs; generate claude-review-result.json, adjudication.md, construction-inspection.json; run final closeout validation) — these must complete before commit/closeout but do not block this review. Verdict reflects review-step satisfaction only; final human approval for any enterprise trust claim remains required and is out of scope of this receipt.",
